en:
Join the hundreds of researchers from around
           the world who are part of the Open Specy community by
           analyzing, sharing, processing, and identifying
           their Raman and IR spectra. These services are free and open source thanks to our partners:
uz:
Atrofdagi yuzlab tadqiqotchilarga qo'shiling
           tomonidan Open Specy hamjamiyatining bir qismi bo'lgan dunyo
           tahlil qilish, almashish, qayta ishlash va aniqlash
           ularning Raman va IQ spektrlari. Hamkorlarimiz tufayli ushbu xizmatlar bepul va ochiq manba hisoblanadi:

en:
In Brief: To use the tool upload a csv, asp, jdx, spc, or spa file to the upload file tab.
                                  If csv, one column should be named 'wavenumber' (in units of 1/cm) and another named 'intensity'.
                                  You can smooth your data using an SG filter, baseline correct your data using the polynomial order of iModPolyFit, and restrict the wavelength range for the match.
                                  The result will be compared to an internal Raman or FTIR spectra library. The strongest 1000 matches along with your
                                  uploaded or processed data will be presented in an interactive plot and table. For more details click the button below
                                  or watch the detailed instructional video.
uz:
Qisqacha ma'lumot: Asbobdan foydalanish uchun csv, asp, jdx, spc yoki spa faylini yuklash fayli yorlig'iga yuklang.
                                  Agar csv bo'lsa, bitta ustun "to'lqin raqami" (1/sm birliklarida) va boshqasi "intensivlik" deb nomlanishi kerak.
                                  Siz SG filtri yordamida maʼlumotlaringizni tekislashingiz, iModPolyFit polinom tartibidan foydalanib maʼlumotlaringizni bazaviy tuzatishingiz va oʻyin uchun toʻlqin uzunligi diapazonini cheklashingiz mumkin.
                                  Natija ichki Raman yoki FTIR spektrlari kutubxonasi bilan taqqoslanadi. Siz bilan birga eng kuchli 1000 ta o'yin
                                  yuklangan yoki qayta ishlangan ma'lumotlar interaktiv syujet va jadvalda taqdim etiladi. Batafsil ma'lumot olish uchun quyidagi tugmani bosing
                                  yoki batafsil o'quv videosini tomosha qiling.

en:
Reference spectra was sourced from open access resources
           online, peer reviewed publications, and corporate donations. In the future
           spectra that is uploaded to the tool will be incorporated to the reference
           library to make it even better.
uz:
Yo'naltiruvchi spektrlar ochiq kirish manbalaridan olingan
           onlayn, ko'rib chiqilgan nashrlar va korporativ xayriyalar. Kelajakda
           asbobga yuklangan spektrlar havolaga kiritiladi
           kutubxonani yanada yaxshilash uchun.

en:
To share spectra upload a file to the upload file tab. If you selected Share a copy of your spectra will be sent to the Community
           Data Warehouse on Open Science Framework. To add additional metadata, 
           fill in the avaliable metadata fields and click -Share Data-. The 
           spectra file that you uploaded along with your responses will be copied 
           to the a -With Metadata- subfolder at the link below. All shared data holds 
           a Creative Commons Attribution License 4.0.
uz:
Spektrlarni baham ko'rish uchun faylni yuklash fayl yorlig'iga yuklang. Agar siz ulashishni tanlasangiz, spektrlaringizning nusxasi hamjamiyatga yuboriladi
           Open Science Framework bo'yicha ma'lumotlar ombori. Qo'shimcha metama'lumotlarni qo'shish uchun,
           mavjud metama'lumotlar maydonlarini to'ldiring va "Ma'lumotlarni almashish" tugmasini bosing. The
           javoblaringiz bilan birga yuklagan spektr fayli nusxalanadi
           quyidagi havoladagi -With Metadata- pastki jildga o'ting. Barcha umumiy maʼlumotlar saqlanadi
           Creative Commons Attribution License 4.0.

en:
All parameters in this tool are tested to validate that 
           the tool is functioning as best as possible and determine the best default 
           parameters to use. Our current validation proceedure includes correcting 
           duplicated entries in the reference libraries, checking for spectra in 
           metadata that isn't in the spectral library, and ensuring the the default 
           parameters provide over 80% accuracy in the first match.
uz:
Ushbu vositadagi barcha parametrlar buni tasdiqlash uchun sinovdan o'tkaziladi
           asbob iloji boricha yaxshi ishlaydi va eng yaxshi standartni aniqlaydi
           foydalanish uchun parametrlar. Bizning joriy tekshirish jarayoni tuzatishni o'z ichiga oladi
           ma'lumot kutubxonalarida takrorlangan yozuvlar, spektrlarni tekshirish
           spektral kutubxonada bo'lmagan metadata va standartni ta'minlash
           parametrlar birinchi o'yinda 80% dan ortiq aniqlikni ta'minlaydi.

en:
If you like, we share your uploaded spectra and settings with the spectroscopy community.
           By default, all data will be licensed under Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial 4.0 International (CC BY-NC 4.0).
           Uploaded spectra will appear here: https://osf.io/rjg3c
uz:
Agar xohlasangiz, yuklangan spektr va sozlamalaringizni spektroskopiya hamjamiyatiga baham ko'ramiz.
           Odatiy boʻlib, barcha maʼlumotlar Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial 4.0 International (CC BY-NC 4.0) boʻyicha litsenziyalanadi.
           Yuklangan spektrlar bu yerda paydo bo'ladi: https://osf.io/rjg3c

en:
Upload Raman or FTIR spectrum files as a csv, jdx, spc, or spa. A csv file is preferred. If a csv, the file must contain one column labeled 'wavenumber' in units of (1/cm) and another column labeled 'intensity' in absorbance units.
            If jdx, spc, spa, or 0 the file should be a single absorbance spectrum with wavenumber in (1/cm). These files will not always work perfectly because they are tricky to read so double check them in another software.
            Hit the 'Test Data' button to download a sample Raman spectrum.
uz:
Raman yoki FTIR spektrli fayllarni csv, jdx, spc yoki spa sifatida yuklang. csv faylga afzallik beriladi. Agar csv bo'lsa, faylda (1/sm) birliklarda "to'lqin raqami" deb nomlangan bitta ustun va absorbans birliklarida "intensivlik" deb nomlangan boshqa ustun bo'lishi kerak.
            Agar jdx, spc, spa yoki 0 bo'lsa, fayl to'lqin soni (1/sm) bo'lgan yagona absorbans spektri bo'lishi kerak. Ushbu fayllar har doim ham mukammal ishlamaydi, chunki ularni o'qish qiyin, shuning uchun ularni boshqa dasturda ikki marta tekshiring.
            Raman spektrining namunasini yuklab olish uchun "Ma'lumotlarni sinovdan o'tkazish" tugmasini bosing.

en:
If the uploaded spectrum is not in absorbance units, 
           use this input to specify the units to convert from.Open Specy can 
           adjust reflectance or transmittance spectra to Absorbance units using 
           this drop down in the upload file tab. All of the preceding tabs 
           assume that the data is in absorbance units so you should make the 
           correction before continuing if needed. The transmittance adjustment 
           uses the log10(1/T) calculation which does not correct for system 
           and particle characteristics. The reflectance adjustment uses the 
           Kubelka-Munk equation (1-R)2/(2*R). We assume that the reflectance 
           is formatted as a percent from 1-100 and first correct the intensity by dividing by 100
           so that it fits the form expected by the equation.
           If none is selected, Open Specy assumes that the uploaded data is 
           an absorbance spectrum.
uz:
Agar yuklangan spektr absorbans birliklarida bo'lmasa,
           dan konvertatsiya qilinadigan birliklarni belgilash uchun ushbu kiritishdan foydalaning.Open Specy mumkin
           yordamida aks ettirish yoki o'tkazuvchanlik spektrlarini Absorbans birliklariga moslang
           bu yuklash fayl yorlig'ida ochiladi. Oldingi barcha tablar
           Ma'lumotlar absorbans birliklarida deb faraz qiling, shuning uchun siz buni qilishingiz kerak
           agar kerak bo'lsa, davom ettirishdan oldin tuzatish. O'tkazuvchanlikni sozlash
           tizim uchun to'g'ri kelmaydigan log10(1/T) hisobini ishlatadi
           va zarrachalarning xususiyatlari. Ko'zguni sozlash dan foydalanadi
           Kubelka-Munk tenglamasi (1-R)2/(2*R). Biz aks ettirishni taxmin qilamiz
           1 dan 100 gacha foiz sifatida formatlanadi va avval intensivlikni 100 ga bo'lish orqali to'g'rilaydi
           shuning uchun u tenglama tomonidan kutilgan shaklga mos keladi.
           Hech biri tanlanmagan bo'lsa, Open Specy yuklangan ma'lumotlarni shunday deb hisoblaydi
           absorbsiya spektri.

en: This is a sample spectrum that can be uploaded to the tool for testing it out and understanding how the csv files should be formatted.
uz: Bu sinash va csv fayllarni qanday formatlash kerakligini tushunish uchun asbobga yuklanishi mumkin bo'lgan namuna spektridir.

en:
We share any uploaded spectra and metadata with the spectroscopy community if you fill out the metadata here and select share.
           Uploaded spectra and metadata will appear here: https://osf.io/rjg3c
uz:
Agar metamaʼlumotlarni shu yerda toʻldirib, “Ulashish”ni tanlasangiz, biz har qanday yuklangan spektr va metamaʼlumotlarni spektroskopiya hamjamiyatiga baham koʻramiz.
           Yuklangan spektrlar va metamaʼlumotlar shu yerda paydo boʻladi: https://osf.io/rjg3c

en: Upload some data to get started...
Smooth, Baseline Correct, and Download Processed Spectra
uz: Silliq, asosiy to'g'ri va qayta ishlangan spektrlarni yuklab oling

en: Some users may wish to save a copy of their processed spectrum. This button downloads the processed spectrum as a csv file.
uz: Ba'zi foydalanuvchilar o'zlarining qayta ishlangan spektrining nusxasini saqlashni xohlashlari mumkin. Bu tugma qayta ishlangan spektrni csv fayli sifatida yuklab oladi.

en: This smoother can enhance the signal to noise ratio of the data and uses a Savitzky-Golay filter with 12 running data points and the polynomial specified.
uz: Ushbu silliqlash moslamasi ma'lumotlarning shovqinga signal nisbatini oshirishi mumkin va 12 ishlaydigan ma'lumot nuqtasi va ko'rsatilgan polinomga ega Savitzky-Golay filtridan foydalanadi.

en: This baseline correction routine has two options for baseline correction, 1) the polynomial imodpolyfit procedure to itteratively find the baseline of the spectrum using a polynomial fit to the entire region of the spectra. 2) manual lines can be drawn using the line tool on the plot and the correct button will use the lines to subtract the baseline.
uz: Ushbu bazaviy tuzatish tartibida bazaviy tuzatishning ikkita varianti mavjud: 1) polinom imodpolifit protsedurasi spektrning butun mintaqasiga polinom mosligidan foydalanib, takroriy ravishda spektrning asosiy chizig'ini topish. 2) chizmadagi chiziq vositasi yordamida qo'lda chiziqlar chizish mumkin va to'g'ri tugma chiziqlardan asosiy chiziqni olib tashlash uchun foydalanadi.

en: Restricting the spectral range can remove regions of spectrum where no peaks exist and improve matching
uz: Spektral diapazonni cheklash spektrning cho'qqilari bo'lmagan hududlarini olib tashlashi va moslikni yaxshilashi mumkin

en: Identify Spectrum Using the Reference Library
This selection will determine whether the FTIR or Raman matching library is used. Choose the spectrum type that was uploaded.
uz: Ushbu tanlov FTIR yoki Raman mos kutubxonasidan foydalanilganligini aniqlaydi. Yuklangan spektr turini tanlang.

en: This selection will determine whether the uploaded (not processed) spectrum or the spectrum processed using the processing tab is used in the spectrum match.
uz: Ushbu tanlov yuklangan (qayta ishlanmagan) spektr yoki qayta ishlash yorlig'i yordamida qayta ishlangan spektr spektrga mos kelishini aniqlaydi.

en: This selection will determine whether the library you are matching to consists of the full spectrum or only spectrum peaks.
uz: Ushbu tanlov siz mos keladigan kutubxona to'liq spektrdan yoki faqat spektr cho'qqilaridan iboratligini aniqlaydi.

uz: Spektroskopiyani inqilob qilish maqsadimizga erishishimizga yordam bering.
